Package com.amazon.clouddrive.model

These classes are used to parametrize requests to Amazon Cloud Drive and are deserialized as responses to requests made.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CloudDriveRequest
    All Amazon Cloud Drive requests inherit from CloudDriveRequest.
    CloudDriveResponse
    Root interface for some responses.
    IEditableNode
    Editable portion of the node
    IGetChangesResponse<T extends INode>
    Response returned from AmazonCloudDrive.getChanges(GetChangesRequest).
    INode
    The object which represents all digital assets.
    NodeListingResponse<T extends INode>
    Response that contains a listing of nodes.

  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Suppress
    When uploading files, there is an optional query parameter which will tell Amazon Cloud Drive to suppress a particular operation.

Package com.amazon.clouddrive.model Description

These classes are used to parametrize requests to Amazon Cloud Drive and are deserialized as responses to requests made. See AmazonCloudDrive for making those requests.
